In addition, we've seen capacity prices decline. The stability and certainty provided by a contract better address -- clearly better address the financial challenges of these plants without being exposed to all this market volatility. In addition, the term of the contract helps with things like capital planning and the efficiency of that, obviously, our workforce personnel planning. And we just think it's a much more certain outcome and a better way here.

Steve Fleishman -- Wolfe Research -- Analyst

